OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F468A1778234502
OL,3,CWelsh leaders begin last full day of
OL,4,Ccampaigning ahead of pivotal election
OL,6,FSpeaking on ITV's Sharp End on
OL,7,FTuesday, 5 May, party candidate Heledd
OL,8,FFychan said "the momentum is with
OL,9,FPlaid Cymru," but stressed that the
OL,10,Fresults show "just how close it is"
OL,11,Fbetween the party and Reform UK.
OL,13,FWelsh Conservative leader Darren
OL,14,FMillar is also in the north,
OL,15,Fcampaigning in Abergele. His party
OL,16,Fsecured a modest increase in their
OL,17,Fvote share to 9%, which would
OL,18,Ftranslate into four seats, placing
OL,19,Fthem in fourth.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/7
