PN,46804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F468A1778234502
OL,3,CWelsh leaders begin last full day of
OL,4,Ccampaigning ahead of pivotal election
OL,6,FHer party has continued the trend of
OL,7,Fpolling in third place at 12%, which
OL,8,Fwould yield 12 seats. However, the
OL,9,Fpoll predicts Morgan would lose her
OL,10,Fseat in Ceredigion Penfro.
OL,12,FSpeaking to ITV Cymru Wales, she said:
OL,13,F"This is not a fight between Reform
OL,14,Fand Plaid Cymru, Welsh Labour is right
OL,15,Fin there."
OL,17,FShe added: "We are the only party
OL,18,Fthat's set out a realistic proposal
OL,19,Ffor how we would govern this country.
OL,20,FEverything else is a risk."
