OL,3,CWelsh leaders begin last full day of
OL,4,Ccampaigning ahead of pivotal election
OL,6,FAnthony Slaughter, the Green Party
OL,7,Fleader in Wales, is in Cardiff. His
OL,8,Fparty has dropped into fifth place at
OL,9,F8% which, in this round of results,
OL,10,Fwould net them just two seats in
OL,11,FCaerdydd Ffynnon Taf and Caerdydd
OL,12,FPenarth.
OL,14,FSpeaking on ITV's Sharp End, party
OL,15,Fcandidate Phil Davies argued it is
OL,16,Fimportant for people to "vote for who
OL,17,Fthey want to be in the Senedd."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/7
